definition: Georgetown/(the spelling 喬治敦|乔治敦 is more common)
to rule/to govern/to manage/to control/to harness (a river)/to treat (a disease)/to wipe out (a pest)/to punish/to research
Georgetown University in Washington D.C., famous as quality Jesuit university and for its basketball team

sentences.english: Both Georgetown and the Chinese government are likewise playing things safe.
sentences.chinese: 喬治城大學和中國政府同樣對此事持謹慎態度。

sentences.english: 1789- Georgetown University was established in present-day Washington DC.
sentences.chinese: 1789年的今天，喬治城大學在當今的華盛頓成立。

sentences.english: It cost less than their city home on a one-acre lot in Georgetown.
sentences.chinese: 它的成本就在喬治城一英畝很多比他們的城市家庭少。

sentences.english: At the time I was an undergrad at Georgetown University studying international relations.
sentences.chinese: 當時，我是美國喬治城大學的學生，主修國際關係。
